ark change. Keating ably ties history to incisive and sympathetic observations drawn from his travels and personal interviews with residents, political leaders, and scholars in each of these "invisible countries."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aBoundariesxAnthropological aspects. 0aBoundaries. 0aSovereignty. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Geography.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235050423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235050.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles